data.title: Albert King ~ Songs List
data.text:
Rolling Stone: "...From the opening doom-ladden guitar intro into `Honky Tonk Woman' through King's blues-ballad treatment of `Like A Road Leading Home' he convinces, both vocally and musically, that the fire is still there..."

2.Bay Area Blues

5.For The Love of A Woman

8.Going Back To Iuka

9.Like A Road Leading Home

Down Beat: 4 stars out of 5 -- "White-hot flames rage, subside and rage again as they lob grenade after grenade into impromptu arrangements....Their respect for each other is palpable..."

2.Old Times

3.Pride and Joy

Living Blues: "[The album] rivals 1967's BORN UNDER A BAD SIGN as King's greatest album and was the highest charting album of his career..."
